This project incorporates, depends on, or is derived from the following
open-source software. Each component retains its original license.


1. Apache Guacamole Server (guacd)
   - Source:  https://github.com/apache/guacamole-server
   - License: Apache License 2.0
   - Usage:   The `guacd/Dockerfile` builds a custom image from the official
              Apache Guacamole server source code. The Dockerfile modifies
              build arguments (FreeRDP version) and adds Kerberos system
              packages. No source code of guacamole-server is committed to
              this repository; it is cloned at build time.

2. guacamole-common-js
   - Source:  https://www.npmjs.com/package/guacamole-common-js
   - License: Apache License 2.0
   - Usage:   Frontend npm dependency for HTML5 Canvas rendering of
              Guacamole protocol streams and session recording playback.

3. FreeRDP
   - Source:  https://github.com/FreeRDP/FreeRDP
   - License: Apache License 2.0
   - Usage:   Linked at compile time inside the custom guacd image as the
              RDP protocol backend (version 3).

4. MIT Kerberos (krb5)
   - Source:  https://web.mit.edu/kerberos/
   - License: MIT License
   - Usage:   Runtime library installed in the guacd and backend containers
              for GSSAPI/Kerberos authentication.


